# Facade Design

- Facades MUST have no argument or only one argument that follows the pattern `src/CSharpModulith.Capability.<CapabilityName>/Application/Requests/<MethodName>Request.php`
- Facades MUST have void or only one return type that follows the pattern `src/CSharpModulith.Capability.<CapabilityName>/Application/Responses/<MethodName>Response.php`
- Those objects must take only primitives
- Those objects must be read only and final
- Facades SHOULD favor broad interfaces over concrete methods, e.g. batch over single operations if feasible
- The response objects must implement static methods
  - `withSuccess()` with any number of arguments setting the required data.
  - `withFailure(<CapabilityName>Failure $failure, ?string $message)` the method CAN have additional arguments

## Specification Block

Every facade interface must document all of methods with a first line `Specification:`, followed by an empty line, then followed by a list of things the facade methods will do, only behavior, business logic should be describered here.

### Specification Block Example

```php
/**
 * Specification:
 * 
 * - First line
 * - Second line
 *   - Sub-line
 */
public function checkout()
{

}
```

## Facade Tests

- Facades MUST be fully tested, all possible outcomes MUST be tested
- Facades tests are integration tests, don't mock anything except external systems.
- Facade testS MUST be placed in `tests/Capability/<CapabilityName>/Application/`







